oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Panoramic Photograph of Supply Co., 114th FA, 30th Div.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: 114th Field Artillery was part of the 30th Division. The 30th Division was composed primarily of National Guard units from Tennessee and the Carolinas. This panoramic photograph was taken at Newport News, Virginia upon the return of the Supply Company from Europe in March 1919. The image belonged to 1st Class Machinist Robert Jackson and it is assumed that he is somewhere in the photograph. Jackson was born in Dekalb County, Tennessee but spent most of his life in Wilson County, Tennessee.
